Figure: Searching the Design Hierarchy
The -hierarchical search is equivalent to manually performing a search at each level of the hierarchy, using the current\_instance command to set the search scope to a particular hierarchical instance, and return all the objects that match the specified name pattern at that level. The following Tcl code, based on Ge...
set result {}
foreach hcell [list "" A B A/a1 A/a2 B/b1 B/b2] {
    current_instance $hcell ;# Move scope to $hcell
    set result [concat $result [get_cells <pattern>]]
    current_instance ;# Return scope to design top-level
}

